AmaZulu King MisuZulu KaZwelithini. JOHANNESBURG - King Misuzulu kaZwelithini's coronation has been postponed. That is as Kwazulu-Natal battles the effects of the catastrophic floods. The coronation was scheduled to take place in late May. Prime Minister of AmaZulu nation Mangosuthu Buthelezi says now is the time to focus on healing and rebuilding. READ: King's Coronation | WATCH | Ceremony to boost local economy He says King Misuzulu expressed his strong conviction that the celebration of coronation must be postponed. Buthelezi says he informed President Cyril Ramaphosa and says that the President has accepted the decision. A new date will be set after the Royal family has consulted with the President. The province is reeling from the devastating floods that killed over 400 people and caused substantial damage to infrastructure.